other_tests.findings: Centrally located polygonal intraluminal filling defect within the lower third of the common bile duct correlating to a common bile duct stone. No intra- or extra-hepatic biliary dilatation. No abnormal biliary caliber changes or stricture noted. Two calcified gallstones projecting lateral to the common bile duct.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Patient is seen to have a common bile duct stent in place on subsequent images.
